, 
<figureCitation box="[256,286,1655,1679]" captionStart="FIGURES 25–33" captionStartId="58.[151,263,1338,1361]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,193,1317]" captionTargetId="figure-153@58.[151,1435,193,1317]" captionTargetPageId="58" captionText="FIGURES 25–33. ♀. 25, Debilos palaior sp. nov., fore wing, dorsal. Specimen from Ecuador, Morona-Santiago, Cordillera de Cutucú, 28.III.1981 (BMNH). 26–28, fore and hind wings, dorsal, Holotypes. 26, D. soror (Trentepohl). 27, D. orthum sp. nov. 28, D. frater sp. nov., arrow: ramellus. 29, hind wing, dorsal, D. curtuvenatum sp. nov., Holotype. 30–33, fore and hind wings, dorsal. 30, D. trochanteratum (Szépligeti). Specimen from Brazil, RO, Candeias do Jamari, 28.I–4.II.2006 (UFES). 31, D. indistinctum sp. nov., Holotype. 32, D. prionilix sp. nov., Holotype. 33, D. typurum sp. nov., Holotype. Illustrations not to scale. Fig. 26 photographed by Berthil B. Longo." pageId="33" pageNumber="34">25</figureCitation>
